  "body": "### Issue\r\nExisting community invites are not reflecting updated permission requirements when permission criteria are changed. Sending a new request does reflect the new permissions.\r\n\r\n### Summary\r\nAfter creating a token-gated community with 'become a member' permissions on desktop, sending an invite on desktop, and opening that invite on mobile, editing the token requirements on desktop does not update the invite on mobile.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Create a token-gated community with 'become a member' permissions (desktop).\r\n2. Send an invite (desktop).\r\n3. Open that invite (mobile).\r\n4. Edit the token requirements (desktop).\r\n5. Check the invite again (mobile).\r\n\r\n### Actual Result\r\nThe token requirements are not updated on the mobile invite.\r\n\r\n### Expected Result\r\nThe mobile invite should show the new token requirements.\r\n\r\nNote: Sending a new request will correctly display the updated requirements.",
